          ],
          "returnType": "void",
          "description": "Invoke callback for every leaf whose fat AABB overlaps the query AABB. Allocation-free: traversal uses a persistent internal stack. Invocation ORDER is tree-shape-dependent — callers needing determinism must normalise their own output (physics does via its final id-sort). NOT re-entrant: because the traversal stack is a single persistent field shared across all calls on this instance, a callback must not call query/queryPoint again on the SAME tree instance. The nested call resets the shared stack and silently truncates the outer traversal, yielding an incomplete result set with no error thrown."
        },
